  "reviewed_vet": {
    "root_cause_summary": "Three unbounded `for (;;)` loops in `dissect_rfc7468` call `tvb_find_line_end(tvb, offset, -1, &next_offset, FALSE)`. When `offset` is past the end of the tvbuff and reassembly is disabled (FALSE), `tvb_find_line_end` returns a zero-length line (length 0) without advancing `next_offset` — so `next_offset == offset` and the loop never progresses, causing infinite spin (CWE-835: Loop with Unreachable Exit Condition) and denial of service.",
    "vulnerability_mechanism": "The function `dissect_rfc7468` contains three `for (;;)` loops (lines 153, 215, 260 in vulnerable version) that iterate over lines of the input tvbuff. Each loop calls `tvb_find_line_end(tvb, offset, -1, &next_offset, FALSE)`. Per the commit message: when past the end of the tvbuff, `tvb_find_line_end` returns a zero-length line and does NOT advance `next_offset`. Because the loop lacks a bounds check on `offset`, the loop condition `for (;;)` is unconditionally true, resulting in an infinite loop. An attacker can trigger this by sending a packet or crafted capture file that causes the dissector to read past the tvbuff boundary — the loop spins forever, consuming CPU and causing denial of service (CWE-835). No removed critical sequence exists; the vulnerability is purely a missing input validation guard (missing tvbuff bounds check before loop progression).",
    "fix_mechanism": "Replace all three `for (;;)` loop headers with `while (tvb_offset_exists(tvb, offset))`. This adds a tvbuff bounds check as the loop continuation condition: before each iteration, verify that `offset` is still within the valid tvbuff data. If `offset` has advanced past the end (or was already past the end), the loop terminates immediately. The fix preserves all original loop body logic (line parsing, encapsulation boundary detection, base64 decoding) unchanged.",
    "scope": {
      "files": ["epan/dissectors/file-rfc7468.c"],
      "functions": ["dissect_rfc7468(tvbuff_t *tvb, packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *tree, void *data)"],
      "components": ["RFC 7468 dissector"],
